Space Law Proverb Alphabet ~

A — Asteroid salvage belongs to the swift beam.Speed determines ownership in unmapped sectors.
B — Breach of orbit voids the baseline insurance.Departing from designated flight paths yields total liability.
C — Cargo unsealed in transit is cargo shared.Implied consent governs open holds during deep sleep.
D — Derelict hulls hold no citizen rights.Abandoned vessels forfeit legal protection against recycling crews.
E — Ejection without a beacon is capital malice.Spacewalking a prisoner without telemetry equals murder.
F — Fuel priority belongs to the outbound hull.Vessels leaving system limits carry sovereign docking preference.
G — Gravity wells dictate the local tax venue.Jurisdiction lands wherever the primary mass pulls hardest.
H — Hyper-lane drifting incurs a triple tariff.Straying from designated light-beams disrupts public commerce.
I — Ion damage is an Act of Cosmos.Solar storms offer zero basis for contract litigation.
J — Jettisoned waste must bear a tracking sigil.Unmarked debris fields carry severe corporate pollution fines.
K — Kinetic impacts require immediate silver payout.Micro-meteoroid shield failure by neglect demands instant barter.
L — Light-year delays do not pause interest accrual.Debt compounds continuously, despite time dilation effects.
M — Mutiny vanishes once the airlock opens.Commanders hold absolute executive summary justice at sea.
N — Nebula mining requires a secondary beacon.Gas harvesting without visual warnings voids rescue bonds.
O — Oxygen rationing overrides any labor contract.Life support emergency measures supersede standard crew hours.
P — Planetary landing requires a clean hull certificate.Exobiotic contamination brings permanent quarantine of assets.
Q — Quantum encryption keys cannot be subpoenaed.Lost codes remain legally vacant under sector code.
R — Radiation leaks require instant hull isolation.Quarantine protocols permanently sever contaminated sector access.
S — Sub-light salvage splits sixty-forty for crews.Standard division rules protect engineers over corporate owners.
T — Telemetry logs provide the final verdict.Black box data overrides all eyewitness crew testimony.
U — Uncharted jumps are taken at owner peril.Insurance networks explicitly deny blind hyperspace travel claims.
V — Vacuum-born infants hold multi-sector citizenship.Birth in deep space grants dual planetary entry rights.
W — Warp-drive hum is legally domestic noise.Crew members cannot sue for engine-room acoustic damage.
X — Xeno-trade requires a standard three-party bond.First-contact commerce demands a neutral planetary escrow agent.
Y — Yield signs apply to lower-mass vessels.Heavy freight haulers always maintain interstellar right-of-way.
Z — Zero-gravity storage is subject to drift loss.Warehouse facilities take no blame for minor magnetic migration.
